I agree with the layout example and would add that prototype based languages that unify method calls with attribute lookups (through message sends) give you both:<p><pre><code>  SomeController := Controller clone do(
    layout := "template"
  )

  SomeController := Controller clone do(
    layout := method(
        if(params at("foo") == "bar", "foo-template", "template")
    )
  )
</code></pre>
This way the framework would send the layout message to the cloned SomeController object and get the proper layout name for either case.
